-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, FHB Are Active in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-16T16:45:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-refiner-mol-are-active-in-budapest.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock  index 
fell 2 percent to 18,749.76 by the close in Budapest. The
following were among the most active equities in the Hungarian
market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, fell 3.9
percent to 3,870 forint after UBS AG downgraded its
recommendation for the stock to “neutral” from “buy” and on
concern  Greece  won’t get European aid in time to make its debt
payments.  Foldhitel es Jelzalogbank Nyrt . (FHB HB), a Hungarian
mortgage lender, declined 1.2 percent to 504 forint as delays to
Greece’s rescue curbed demand for riskier emerging-market
financial assets.  To contact the reporter on this story:
